{#-
  SDD.md.j2 — Jinja2 template for a Software Design Document.

  This template owns ALL standard SDD scaffolding: section numbering,
  standard section titles ("Introduction", "Purpose of the Document",
  "System Overview", "Detailed Design for X", "Data Dictionary",
  "Traceability"), boilerplate lead-in sentences, table headers, and
  the auto-generated "Document Overview" section.

  Data is supplied by `doc/Project.xml` and exposed by
  `tools/render_doc.py` as the `project` namespace:

      project.metadata.{title,version,date,author}
      project.name           — long project name
      project.short_name     — short project name
      project.sdd            — the <sdd> data payload (see schema in
                               doc/Project.xml comment header)

  The template is intentionally generic: any project that fills in
  <sdd> with the same shape gets a complete SDD. To adapt to a
  different SDD outline, edit the standard headings below; the data
  schema does not need to change.

  Editing tips (literal Jinja delimiters shown with spaces):
    * Comments use   { # - ... - # }   and are stripped from the output.
    * Control tags use   { % - ... - % }   for if / for / macro blocks.
    * Substitutions use   { { ... } }   to inject a value.
    * Trim markers "-" suppress surrounding whitespace.
    * The `indent(N)` filter indents continuation lines so multi-line
      bullet bodies render as one bullet item in markdown.
    * Recommended VS Code extension: "Better Jinja"
      (samuelcolvin.jinjahtml) for *.j2 syntax highlighting.
-#}
{#- ===================== helper macros ===================== -#}
{%- macro module_heading(m) -%}
{%- if m.path -%}[{{ m.path }}](../{{ m.path }}){%- else -%}{{ m.title }}{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- macro bullet(body, indent_width=4) -%}
*   {{ body | indent(indent_width) }}
{%- endmacro -%}

{#- Verbose form: Purpose/Pre/Post/Returns/Logic/Notes nested under bullet.
    Used when the data carries a <purpose> child. Trailing blank line
    separates consecutive verbose entries. -#}
{% macro fn_block_verbose(fn) -%}
*   **`{{ fn.signature }}`**
    *   Purpose: {{ fn.purpose | indent(8) }}
{% if fn.pre %}    *   Pre-condition: {{ fn.pre | indent(8) }}
{% endif -%}
{% if fn.post %}    *   Post-condition: {{ fn.post | indent(8) }}
{% endif -%}
{% if fn.returns %}    *   Return Value: {{ fn.returns | indent(8) }}
{% endif -%}
{% if fn.logic %}    *   Logic:
{% for step in fn.logic %}        {{ loop.index }}.  {{ step | indent(12) }}
{% endfor -%}
{% endif -%}
{% if fn.notes %}    *   Notes: {{ fn.notes | indent(8) }}
{% endif %}
{% endmacro -%}

{#- Compact form: signature + summary inline; optional inline numbered
    steps and optional plain-prose notes. No trailing blank line. -#}
{% macro fn_block_compact(fn) -%}
*   **`{{ fn.signature }}`**{% if fn.summary %} — {{ fn.summary | indent(4) }}{% endif %}
{% if fn.logic %}{% for step in fn.logic %}    {{ loop.index }}.  {{ step | indent(8) }}
{% endfor -%}
{% endif -%}
{% if fn.notes %}
    {{ fn.notes | indent(4) }}
{% endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- macro fn_block(fn) -%}
{% if fn.purpose %}{{ fn_block_verbose(fn) }}{% else %}{{ fn_block_compact(fn) }}{% endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
